President Samia Suluhu Hassan has reappointed Dr Hedwiga Swai as the Chairperson of the Tanzania Aids Commission (TACAIDS)’s Board of Directors. A statement released by the State House’s Directorate of Communications in Dodoma on Friday said Dr Swai has been reappointed following expiration of the first term. Meanwhile, the President has named Sophia Kaduma as Board chairperson of the Public Service Employment Secretariat (PSRS)’s Board. The appointments of Dr Swai and Kaduma come into effect from today, April 23, 2021.